# id: MemoryBlockIterator -> public boolean nextBlock() throws IOException_
commentText: Move the iterator to the next memory block. The next memory block starts at the first element that was not_in the block before. A special case is when no record was in the block before, which happens when this_function is invoked two times directly in a sequence, without calling hasNext() or next in between. Then_the block moves one element.__@return True if a new memory block was loaded, false if there were no further_records and hence no further memory block.__@throws IOException Thrown, when advancing to the next block failed.
